<paragraph blockId="2.[806,1421,496,670]" pageId="2" pageNumber="699">
<emphasis box="[806,925,496,517]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="699">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Urostylids with a specific ventral cirral field that consists of enlarged postoral cirri and delicate left ventral cirri, both of which are derived from the left part of the midventral streaks during morphogenesis; one marginal row on each side; nonmigratory row present.
</paragraph>
